        <div class="course-content-block" data-aos="fade-up">
          <h2>About the Program</h2>
          <p>
            The Bachelor of Science in Nursing (B.Sc. Nursing) is a four-year
            undergraduate degree program that equips students with in-depth
            theoretical knowledge and extensive practical skills in nursing sciences,
            healthcare principles, and patient care.
          </p>
          <p>
            At Merchant Institute of Nursing, the program is designed to develop
            highly skilled, ethical, and compassionate nursing professionals who
            are ready to serve in hospitals, community health settings, and
            specialised healthcare environments.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="course-content-block" data-aos="fade-up">
          <h2>Eligibility Criteria</h2>
          <ul class="course-list">
            <li>Passed 10+2 or equivalent with Physics, Chemistry and Biology</li>
            <li>Minimum 45% aggregate marks (40% for reserved categories)</li>
            <li>Minimum age of 17 years as on 31st December of admission year</li>
            <li>Must have passed English as a subject at 10+2 level</li>
            <li>Medically fit as per INC norms</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="course-content-block" data-aos="fade-up">
          <h2>Program Structure</h2>
          <div class="year-grid">

            <div class="year-card">
              <div class="year-card__num">Year 1</div>
              <p class="year-card__sem">Semester I</p>
              <ul>
                <li>Communicative English</li>
                <li>Applied Anatomy</li>
                <li>Applied Physiology</li>
                <li>Applied Sociology</li>
                <li>Applied Psychology</li>
                <li>Nursing Foundations I</li>
              </ul>
              <p class="year-card__sem">Semester II</p>
              <ul>
                <li>Applied Biochemistry</li>
                <li>Applied Nutrition &amp; Dietetics</li>
                <li>Nursing Foundations II</li>
                <li>Health / Nursing Informatics &amp; Technology</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="year-card">
              <div class="year-card__num">Year 2</div>
              <p class="year-card__sem">Semester III</p>
              <ul>
                <li>Applied Microbiology &amp; Infection Control including Safety</li>
                <li>Pharmacology I</li>
                <li>Pathology I</li>
                <li>Adult Health Nursing I</li>
              </ul>
              <p class="year-card__sem">Semester IV</p>
              <ul>
                <li>Pharmacology II</li>
                <li>Pathology II &amp; Genetics</li>
                <li>Adult Health Nursing II (Geriatrics)</li>
                <li>Professional Values &amp; Ethics (Bioethics)</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="year-card">
              <div class="year-card__num">Year 3</div>
              <p class="year-card__sem">Semester V</p>
              <ul>
                <li>Child Health Nursing I</li>
                <li>Mental Health Nursing I</li>
                <li>Community Health Nursing I</li>
                <li>Nursing Education</li>
                <li>Forensic Nursing &amp; Laws</li>
              </ul>
              <p class="year-card__sem">Semester VI</p>
              <ul>
                <li>Child Health Nursing II</li>
                <li>Mental Health Nursing II</li>
                <li>Nursing Management</li>
                <li>Midwifery I</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="year-card">
              <div class="year-card__num">Year 4</div>
              <p class="year-card__sem">Semester VII</p>
              <ul>
                <li>Community Health Nursing II</li>
                <li>Nursing Research &amp; Statistics</li>
                <li>Midwifery II</li>
              </ul>
              <p class="year-card__sem">Semester VIII</p>
              <ul>
                <li>Internship (Practicum / Residency)</li>
              </ul>
